Sentencas: In this contribution, the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) under high current density load cycles is studied by means of electrical measurements and material analyses.

Sentencas: Our study is an important premise for the application of accelerated life testing (ALT) to SOFC single cells.

Sentencas: We find that during current treatment, a nanoporous domain containing lanthanum zirconate is formed at the cathode-electrolyte interface.
